	<transcript sound="sound1"><![CDATA[When checking and recording temperatures, it is important to follow these steps:<li>For checking core temperatures or surface temperatures use a clean, disinfected, calibrated tip-sensitive digital thermometer;</li><li>Take the core temperature;</li><li>Allow a minimum of 30 seconds contact time to ensure the temperature has stabilised;</li><li>Avoid fat, bone or gristle or container sides;</li><li>Record the temperature in accordance with the HACCP plan;</li><li>For checking surface temperatures only you can use a calibrated digital infra-red thermometer.</li>]]></transcript>
	
	
	
